Name: Mom's Best Pork Chops
Description: Tender and crunchy breaded pork chops are everyone's favorite!
Author: AREJAY59

Name: Buffalo Chicken Mac and Cheese
Description: This Buffalo chicken macaroni and cheese with three kinds of cheese is rich and spicy, great served as a quick and easy weeknight dinner.
Author: Matt R

Name: KISS Salmon
Description: How simple can a salmon recipe be? Just bake fillets with a combination of barbeque sauce and raspberry jam for a delicious and pretty main dish.
Author: cookntaste

Name: Upside-Down Barbeque Meatloaf
Description: Place the meat on top of a layer of barbeque sauce to make Chef John's upside-down barbeque meatloaf, a great twist on the comfort-food classic.
Author: Chef John

Name: Chocolate Pancakes
Description: This is a sweet and slightly gooey chocolate pancake that is great with fresh fruit.
Author: ramie7224

Name: American Lasagna
Description: Lasagna appeals to the eye as well as to the taste buds. Here, ground beef, onion, garlic, basil, tomatoes and a dash of brown sugar make up the sauce, while ricotta, Parmesan, mozzarella, eggs and parsley are the filling for this layered casserole. Prepare up to 2 days in advance, if desired, and chill covered in the refrigerator until ready to bake. Increase the baking time by about 15 minutes.
Author: ETHELMERTZ

Name: Quick Crispy Parmesan Chicken Breasts
Description: This quick and easy recipe for crispy Parmesan chicken breasts goes well with pasta, on a salad, or even on its own.
Author: SUNKIST2

Name: Nikki's Creamy Crock Pot Potato Soup
Description: A creamy, flavorful potato soup, made in the slow cooker, gets extra flavor from bacon and cheese.
Author: Nikki

Name: Tater Tot Taco Casserole
Description: This recipe gives you a Mexican-style version of tater tot casserole.
Author: Irlynda Smith

Name: Boxty with Liver and Bacon
Description: This Irish specialty consists of boxty, traditional potato pancakes, topped with crispy bacon, pan-fried lamb's liver, and wilted cabbage.
Author: jean.isacke

Name: Spinach and Ricotta Tortellini
Description: Homemade spinach and ricotta tortellini, an Italian favorite, is a gourmet vegetarian meal to prepare and it will impress your guests.
Author: alemarsi

Name: Bacon Tater Egg Cups
Description: Bacon and Tater Tots(R) are baked with eggs and veggies in these delicious egg cups, an easy breakfast to take on the run in the morning.
Author: Culinary Envy

Name: Healthy Ham and Egg Muffins
Description: Ham and egg muffins with a touch of feta cheese are a quick and easy breakfast to eat on the run and can be made in advance and frozen.
Author: blue tuberosa

Name: Baked Spinach and Egg White Muffins
Description: Spinach, cheese, and egg white muffins are a great portable breakfast that are quick and easy to prepare for those busy weekday mornings.
Author: cooking made izzy

Name: Chocolate and Guinness(R) Cake
Description: This dense and moist chocolate and Guinness(R) cake has a pudding-like texture that goes down a treat with whipped cream or ice cream.
Author: hybridoriental

Name: Crawfish Pirogue
Description: In this easy Cajun-inspired recipe, Creole-seasoned crawfish stew is spooned into a bread loaf cut into the shape of a pirogue boat.
Author: Caren Lee

Name: Brown Rice Buddha Bowl
Description: Brown rice, vegetables, tofu and chickpeas are topped with a spicy Thai basil dressing and toasted sesame seeds in this fresh Buddha bowl.
Author: Buckwheat Queen

Name: Chinese Hand-Pulled Noodles
Description: Chinese hand-pulled noodles, known as lamian in Northwest China, require just 3 ingredients and a little patience to make at home.
Author: Ping Lo

Name: Bratwurst
Description: Learn how to make homemade bratwurst sausages flavored with beer, garlic, and lots of savory spices using this step-by-step recipe.
Author: Brandon

Name: Traditional Dublin Coddle
Description: Smoked streaky bacon, pork sausages, onion, and potatoes simmer together slowly in this traditional coddle recipe from Dublin, Ireland.
Author: J. Boyle

Name: Honey and Rosemary Soda Bread
Description: This half-whole-wheat soda bread flavored with fresh rosemary and honey is best served freshly baked with butter, honey, and a cup of tea.
Author: Chef Liam

Name: Super Shrimp Dip
Description: Cream cheese and mayonnaise blend with shrimp, bacon, celery, and Cheddar cheese in this super dip that's sure to please all your guests.
Author: AJSMOMMA

Name: Wonton Egg Cups
Description: Wonton wrapper cups are filled with eggs, sausage, and Manchego cheese to make these quick and easy bite-size snacks with a pleasing crunch.
Author: Grams

Name: Bacon and Egg Muffins
Description: This bacon, onion, and egg muffin recipe can be customized any way you like to make a grab-and-go breakfast your family will enjoy.
Author: rc2k11

Name: Sausage and Scallion Egg Muffins
Description: Make a batch of these sausage and scallion egg muffins for a week of on-the-go breakfasts or an easy lunch or dinner with a side salad.
Author: Cindy Anschutz Barbieri

Name: Cheesesteak Stromboli
Description: Combine two favorites, cheesesteaks and stromboli, in this recipe that's perfect for a bite-size appetizer that's quick and easy to prepare.
Author: tcasa

Name: Eggplant Bacon
Description: Thin slices of sweet and smoky roasted eggplant are a great vegetarian substitute for bacon in any salads, sandwiches, or breakfast dishes.
Author: Companion

Name: Vegan Eggplant Rollatini
Description: Pretty purple eggplant rollatini with vegan cashew cheese and pesto, baked in tomato sauce, are incredibly tasty, and sure to please anyone.
Author: Juhea Kim

Name: Zeytoon Parvardeh (Persian Olive Pomegranate Dip)
Description: This Persian zeytoon parvardeh, a green olive dip with pomegranate molasses, fresh herbs, and lemon juice, tastes great with pita bread.
Author: Soheila
